                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.003/359</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the Secretary of State of a Conversation With
                        the Chinese Minister</hi> (<hi rend="italic">C. C. Wu</hi>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-05-15">May 15,
                            1930</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Minister Wu called to renew relations. He said he had been talking over certain
                    particular matters with Dr. Hornbeck, and had discussed extraterritoriality with
                    him in a tentative way during my absence. He wanted to know whether he should
                    continue. I said to go ahead and Dr. Hornbeck would take it up with me.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>H[<hi rend="smallcaps">enry</hi>] L. S[<hi rend="smallcaps"
                        >timson</hi>]</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
